The paper discusses the development of HistCite, a tool for analyzing citation networks in the field of bibliometrics. This tool uses various attributes of documents, such as title words, keywords, and author names, to construct intellectual lineages. These attributes are commonly used in the fields of digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), human-computer interaction (cs.HC), social informatics (cs.SI), and computational linguistics (cs.CL). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
